---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About - JamBuddy" description="Learn about the story behind JamBuddy and our mission to enhance musical creativity and collaboration.">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-900 via-black to-gray-900 text-white py-20 rounded-lg relative overflow-hidden" aria-labelledby="about-heading">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none opacity-30 bg-[radial-gradient(circle_at_30%_20%,rgba(60,150,255,0.25),transparent_60%),radial-gradient(circle_at_70%_70%,rgba(0,200,140,0.2),transparent_60%)]"></div>
    <div class="relative max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <h1 id="about-heading" class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6 bg-gradient-to-r from-white via-blue-100 to-green-100 bg-clip-text text-transparent">About JamBuddy</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-300 max-w-4xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        JamBuddy is a focused, distraction‑free practice companion that helps musicians <span class="text-white font-semibold">hear, understand, and create</span> music faster. It blends instant chord recognition, visual rhythm guidance, and organized song & lesson management — built to work fully offline with total privacy.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-10 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3 text-sm" aria-label="Key principles">
        <span class="px-4 py-2 rounded-full bg-white/5 border border-white/10 text-gray-200">Offline • No Ads</span>
        <span class="px-4 py-2 rounded-full bg-white/5 border border-white/10 text-gray-200">One‑Time Purchase</span>
        <span class="px-4 py-2 rounded-full bg-white/5 border border-white/10 text-gray-200">Real‑Time Chord Engine</span>
        <span class="px-4 py-2 rounded-full bg-white/5 border border-white/10 text-gray-200">Multi‑Instrument</span>
        <span class="px-4 py-2 rounded-full bg-white/5 border border-white/10 text-gray-200">Privacy First</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Our Story -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-gray-900 rounded-lg" aria-labelledby="story-heading">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
        <div>
          <h2 id="story-heading" class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-6">Why I Built JamBuddy</h2>
          <div class="prose prose-invert prose-lg text-gray-300 max-w-none">
            <p class="mb-6">I started learning songs the slow, frustrating way—pausing videos, guessing chords, scribbling messy progressions, and losing momentum. Existing apps either locked features behind subscriptions, harvested data, or buried the core tools under clutter.</p>
            <p class="mb-6">So I built what I wished existed: a <strong>fast, offline, no‑nonsense environment</strong> that helps you identify chords as you listen, internalize rhythm visually, loop tricky parts, and log ideas the moment they hit. Teachers began using early builds in group settings and asked for organizational touches—so JamBuddy grew to support both personal practice and classroom flow.</p>
            <p class="mb-0">JamBuddy is still evolving weekly. Every refinement is guided by a simple question: <em>Does this help someone learn or teach music faster with less friction?</em></p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-800 rounded-2xl p-8 border border-purple-500/20 relative overflow-hidden">
          <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-10 bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-500 via-blue-500 to-green-500"></div>
          <div class="relative text-center">
            <div class="w-24 h-24 bg-gradient-to-br from-indigo-600 to-purple-600 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-6 shadow-lg">
              <span class="text-white text-3xl font-bold">JB</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">The Goal</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Remove friction between <em>hearing</em> something inspiring and <em>turning it into music you can play or teach</em>. JamBuddy should feel like a minimal, powerful instrument—not a gamified platform competing for attention.</p>
            <div class="mt-6 grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm text-left">
              <div class="bg-black/30 rounded-lg p-3 border border-white/5"><span class="block text-white font-semibold mb-1">No Dark Patterns</span><span class="text-gray-400">Own it once. No upsells.</span></div>
              <div class="bg-black/30 rounded-lg p-3 border border-white/5"><span class="block text-white font-semibold mb-1">Local Processing</span><span class="text-gray-400">Audio stays on device.</span></div>
              <div class="bg-black/30 rounded-lg p-3 border border-white/5"><span class="block text-white font-semibold mb-1">Fast Feedback</span><span class="text-gray-400">Low‑latency detection.</span></div>
              <div class="bg-black/30 rounded-lg p-3 border border-white/5"><span class="block text-white font-semibold mb-1">Teacher Friendly</span><span class="text-gray-400">Organize songs & sets.</span></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- App Principles -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-gray-900/80 rounded-lg mt-8" aria-labelledby="principles-heading">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h2 id="principles-heading" class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Product Principles</h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-300 max-w-3xl mx-auto">Every design & feature decision filters through these guardrails.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <div class="text-center bg-gray-800 p-6 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/20">
          <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-blue-600 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-6 font-bold text-lg text-white">1</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Beginner Friendly</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">Fast wins build momentum: instant chords, clear rhythm, zero setup overhead. Learn songs—not software.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="text-center bg-gray-800 p-6 rounded-xl border border-green-500/20">
          <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-green-600 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-6 font-bold text-lg text-white">2</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Simple & Useful</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">No dashboards, feed algorithms, or gamified clutter. Only the tools that shorten the gap between listening and playing.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="text-center bg-gray-800 p-6 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/20">
          <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-purple-600 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-6 font-bold text-lg text-white">3</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Constantly Improving</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">Micro-iterations weekly: performance tweaks, detection accuracy boosts, teacher workflow refinements.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- About the Developer -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-gray-900 rounded-lg mt-8" aria-labelledby="developer-heading">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h2 id="developer-heading" class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-4">About the Developer</h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-300 max-w-3xl mx-auto">Student, guitarist-by-obsession, and builder of tools that reduce friction for creative learners.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-12">
        <div class="bg-gray-800 p-8 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/20 max-w-3xl">
          <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 items-start text-left">
            <div class="w-32 h-32 bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-600 to-indigo-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 shadow-lg">
              <span class="text-white text-3xl font-bold">JB</span>
            </div>
            <div class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
              <p>I treat JamBuddy like an instrument. Every millisecond of latency removed and every click saved compounds into smoother practice and teaching sessions. I publish frequent updates and respond directly to feedback—nothing is filtered through support tiers.</p>
              <p>If you’re an educator piloting JamBuddy in a classroom or ensemble setting, I’d love to hear how students are using it and what would accelerate your workflow next.</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">Want to reach out? Use the <a href="/contact" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 underline">contact page</a> or email directly.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- App Features -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-gray-900 text-white rounded-lg mt-8" aria-labelledby="capabilities-heading">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h2 id="capabilities-heading" class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Core Capabilities</h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-300">Foundational tools that speed up the listen → learn → create cycle.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 text-center">
        <div class="bg-gray-800 p-6 rounded-xl border border-gray-700 text-left">
          <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-gray-700 rounded-full mx-auto mb-4 flex items-center justify-center">
            <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-white" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15.536 8.464a5 5 0 010 7.072m2.828-9.9a9 9 0 010 12.728M5.586 15H4a1 1 0 01-1-1v-4a1 1 0 011-1h1.586l4.707-4.707C10.923 3.663 12 4.109 12 5v14c0 .891-1.077 1.337-1.707.707L5.586 15z"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">🎧 Real-Time Chord Recognition</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">Low‑latency detection engine with Circle of Fifths overlay, next‑chord predictions, and integrated tuner. Supports guitar, bass, ukulele, mandolin & more.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-gray-800 p-6 rounded-xl border border-gray-700 text-left">
          <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-gray-700 rounded-full mx-auto mb-4 flex items-center justify-center">
            <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-white" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 8v4l3 3m6-3a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">📚 Practice Tools</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">Visual metronome pulses, strum pattern guidance, tempo adjust without pitch shift, and precision looping for difficult measures.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-gray-800 p-6 rounded-xl border border-gray-700 text-left">
          <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-gray-700 rounded-full mx-auto mb-4 flex items-center justify-center">
            <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-white" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6.253v13m0-13C10.832 5.477 9.246 5 7.5 5S4.168 5.477 3 6.253v13C4.168 18.477 5.754 18 7.5 18s3.332.477 4.5 1.253m0-13C13.168 5.477 14.754 5 16.5 5c1.747 0 3.332.477 4.5 1.253v13C19.832 18.477 18.247 18 16.5 18c-1.746 0-3.332.477-4.5 1.253"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">✍️ Song & Lesson Organization</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">Store lyrics, chord progressions, sheet references, tempo notes, and recordings in one consistent structure.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-gray-800 p-6 rounded-xl border border-gray-700 text-left">
          <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-gray-700 rounded-full mx-auto mb-4 flex items-center justify-center"></div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">🎸 Multi-Instrument Support</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">Switch seamlessly across guitar, ukulele, mandolin, banjo and more with accurate chord shapes & tuning contexts.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Section -->
  <section class="relative py-24 bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-900 via-purple-900 to-blue-900 rounded-xl mt-8 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600/20 via-purple-600/20 to-green-600/20"></div>
    <div class="relative max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white mb-8 bg-gradient-to-r from-white via-blue-100 to-green-100 bg-clip-text text-transparent">Get JamBuddy Now</h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-200 mb-12 max-w-3xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        JamBuddy is now available! Download the app and start learning your favorite songs today.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-6 justify-center">
        <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.jambuddy.app&pcampaignid=web_share" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="group bg-gradient-to-r from-white/20 to-white/10 border-2 border-white/30 backdrop-blur-sm text-white px-10 py-5 rounded-2xl font-bold text-xl hover:from-white/30 hover:to-white/20 transition-all duration-300 flex items-center shadow-2xl transform hover:scale-105">
          <img src="/images/icons/google-play-badge.png" alt="Get it on Google Play" class="h-12 mr-4 transition-transform group-hover:scale-110" />
          Get on Google Play
        </a>
        <a href="/contact" class="bg-gray-800/80 border-2 border-gray-600 text-white px-10 py-5 rounded-2xl font-bold text-xl hover:bg-gray-700/80 hover:border-gray-500 transition-all duration-300 flex items-center backdrop-blur-sm transform hover:scale-105">
          <svg class="w-8 h-8 mr-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M3 8l7.89 5.26a2 2 0 002.22 0L21 8M5 19h14a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2z"></path>
          </svg>
          Send Feedback
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>